      },
      "date": "2012-09-07 04:34:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified\n\nOn Lustre 1.8.8-wc1 node:\n\n # mkfs.lustre --reformat --fsname=testfs1 --mdt --mgs --param=\"mdt.quota_type=ug3 mdt.rootsquash=500:500 mdt.nosquash_nid=10.10.4.135@tcp mdt.group_upcall=/usr/sbin/l_getgroups\" /dev/sdc5\n # mkdir -p /mnt/mds && mount -t lustre /dev/sdc5 /mnt/mds\n # umount /mnt/mds\n\nAfter upgrading, mounting the MGS/MDT succeeded. Dmesg showed that:\n\n Lustre: 5864:0:(obd_config.c:1393:class_config_llog_handler()) For 1.8 interoperability, rename obd type from mds to mdt\n Lustre: Enabling ACL\n Lustre: testfs1-MDT0000: used disk, loading\n Lustre: 5864:0:(mdt_handler.c:4770:mdt_process_config()) Found old param mdt.quota_type, changed it to mdd.quota_type.\n Lustre: 5864:0:(mdt_handler.c:4770:mdt_process_config()) Found old param mdt.rootsquash, changed it to mdt.root_squash.\n Lustre: testfs1-MDT0000: root_squash is set to 500:500\n Lustre: testfs1-MDT0000: nosquash_nids is set to 10.10.4.135@tcp\n Lustre: 5864:0:(mdt_handler.c:4765:mdt_process_config()) For 1.8 interoperability, skip this mdt.group_upcall. It is obsolete.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
